.TH "NAVIGATIONPRECOMMITCONTROLLER.ADDHANDLER" "3JS" "February 9, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationPrecommitController.addHandler \-
NavigationPrecommitController: addHandler() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]addHandler()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]NavigationPrecommitController\f[R] interface allows you to
dynamically add a handler callback function in precommit code, which
will then be run after the navigation has committed.
.PP
This is useful when the navigation workflow depends on information that
is not know until precommit code has started running.
If the precommit and (post\-commit) handler are independent, the handler
can be specified in the in the \f[CR]options.handler\f[R] argument
passed to \f[CR]NavigateEvent.intercept()\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
addHandler(handler);
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]handler\f[R]
A callback function that defines the post\-commit navigation handling
behavior should be; it returns a promise.
.RS
.PP
The handler callback is invoked as though it was passed to the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent.intercept()\f[R] method, and will run after the
\f[CR]currentEntry\f[R] property has been updated.
.RE
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]InvalidStateError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
The originating \f[CR]NavigateEvent\f[R] was not intercepted or has been
canceled.
.IP \(bu 2
The \f[CR]Document\f[R] is not fully active.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]SecurityError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the event \f[CR]isTrusted\f[R] attribute is \f[CR]false\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
For more examples see \f[CR]NavigationPrecommitController\f[R].
.SS Basic usage
This example shows a \f[CR]precommitHandler\f[R] implementation that
fetches data for a page and uses \f[CR]addHandler()\f[R] to add
different handlers based on the page type (the implementations of the
\f[CR]fetchConfig\f[R], \f[CR]setupVideoPlayer()\f[R] and
\f[CR]setupArticleView()\f[R] are not given).
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqnavigate\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  event.intercept({
    \f[B]async\f[R] precommitHandler(controller) {
      \f[B]const\f[R] pageData = \f[B]await\f[R] fetchConfig();
      \f[B]if\f[R] (pageData.type === \(dqvideo\(dq) {
        controller.addHandler(() \f[B]=>\f[R] setupVideoPlayer());
      } \f[B]else\f[R] {
        controller.addHandler(() \f[B]=>\f[R] setupArticleView());
      }
    },
  });
});
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
